## ⚙️ Technical Architecture

- Backend: Python / Flask  
- Frontend: HTML / CSS / JavaScript  
- Cluster: Telnet DX Cluster  
- Analysis: dedicated Python scripts  
- Storage: memory + local JSON files  

No cloud dependency.

---

## 🗂️ Version History

### v6.5
Removal of the `telnetlib` library, replaced by `Telnetlib3` following a suggestion from F5UGQ.  
Introduction of AI with the addition of a **"AI Vocal Brief"** button in the "Solar Indices" panel on index.html — optional, only if you wish to try it.  
Requires a Perplexity API key. Cost: ~€0.01 per call.

### v6.4
Addition of the bandmap on the home page; filtering by band and mode.

### v6.3
Added frequency-based sorting in the HF and VHF DX panels, and an update banner when a new version is available.

### v6.2
Optional addition of callsigns to the watchlist from the dashboard, and support for the new FT2 mode.

### v6.1
New "DXpedition Briefing" page and updates to the index.html maps.

### v6.0 — Stable Release
- Finalization of the **World** page
- Clear separation between Map and World
- Stabilized clustering
- Automatic refresh
- Clarified UX
- User state persistence

> Jump from **v5.7 to v6.0**  
> due to several unpublished trial versions.

### v5.7 — Work-in-progress versions
- World page prototypes
- Scoring adjustments
- Structural fixes

### v5.6
- Experimental introduction of World
- WATCHLIST · Tracking panel

### v5.2
- Introduction of META ANALYSIS

